shared_text:
Spencer High School Activities
August 26 at 10:13 AM ¬∑

Yesterday afternoon, we received the guidelines from Webster City for our game on Friday.

- Spectators in the bleachers are going to be limited to every other row, and no seating in the first two rows. The away bleachers typically sit 700, so will approximately sit 300-350 fans.
- There will also be standing room along the fence.
- Students are allowed to attend and will sit every other row in their section.
- Face coverings are REQUIRED to be worn at all times.
- $5 admission
- Start time is 7:30 pm, National Anthem at 7:15 pm

It is our top priority to keep everyone safe, and it is imperative we respect and follow Webster City's guidelines in place.

If you have any questions please let us know. We are looking forward to getting our season started this Friday and hosting Denison next week!

6th Grade: Ryonna Faulkender

post_text:
Announcements Regarding School Provided Meals

As we finish up the school year, there are some changes to the providing of meals. Below are some important dates regarding meal changes:

Friday, May 22nd, will be the last day of meals provided for the 2019-20 school year.

There will be no meals served during the last week of May (25-29th).

The Summer Meal Program will begin on Monday, June 1st.

Important Information regarding the Summer Meal Program:
We will be serving summer meals from two (2) locations:
Johnson Elementary & Spencer High School (Entrance #9)
Due to construction, we will not be serving meals from Fairview Elementary this summer.
Meals will continue to be served in a ‚ÄúGrab & Go‚Äù format.
Children are not required to be present to get meals.
The schedule and times for the Summer Meal Program will be coming out in the next few days.

Thank you to all of the volunteers who help prepare and serve meals over these past eight weeks!

post_text:
Several FFA students had earned the opportunity to advance to state in various categories! Congratulations to these students!
- Autumn Erdman - Received a first place at Districts and a gold rating and advanced to state with her prepared public speech on the dairy industry.
- The middle school Ag. CSI team consisting of Noah Palmer, Conner Essick, Luke Fisher, Lucas Elser, and Adalyn Schoelerman, received a first place gold rating and advanced to state.
- Keegan Johnson advanced to state with the completion of his Iowa Degree in the Plant Systems Pathway.
- Zack Schoelerman Received gold first place state rating for his Proficiency in Diversified Livestock Production
- Ty Schoelerman received a gold first place state rating for this Proficiency in Beef Production - Entrepreneurship.

Spencer Community Schools is happy to announce parking lot wi-fi for our families in the CCE and Royal areas. We have partnered with Evertek and Royal Telephone Company to provide locations for students to connect their devices.

Students in the Everly area can connect their school devices at the Hap Ketelsen Community Center located at 203 N Main St, Everly, IA 51338. SSID: SCS-Student

Students located in the Royal area can connect their devices at the Royal Telephone Company office located at 307 Main Street, Royal, IA 51357. Once outside please call their phone number at 712-933-2615 to be issued a connection key. SSID: Royal Telephone Guest

Looking for a fun activity to do with your K-5 child at home? Start to learn to code with your child! Join in for "Family Code Week - Home Edition". Sign up for (1) one hour session offered LIVE throughout the week. Do self-paced puzzles as a team, learn 6 Big Ideas in coding and computer science.

http://www.familycodenight.org/

Information from Family Code Night:
Sign up as a Pair, ideally a parent and a child, who will participate as a team.
You‚Äôll need one shared computer, tablet, or Chromebook for each Pair, connected to the internet.
Each session is one hour long and offered ten different times, LIVE, throughout the week of April 13-18.
All attendees receive the Code@Home Kit of free games and activities.

post_text:
Spencer Schools Playgrounds and H.S. Track/Stadium Closed

In conjunction with the City of Spencer and Parks Department, Spencer Schools will be closing all playgrounds as well as access to the Stadium and Track.
I know this may come as an inconvenience, but the health and safety of our kids and community are of utmost importance. It is also important for us to be working together with the city and the steps they are implementing to help reduce the spread of COVID-19.

You will see signage up today at school playgrounds and the stadium. Dale Norton Field will be locked.

post_text:
Our school principals wanted to make sure our students know how much they are appreciated!

"Lincoln Elementary students are the best! They work hard and are excited to learn!" Mrs. Devlaeminck

"Our Tigers at SHS are some of the kindest and most outgoing students! I always feel confident that they represent the community of Spencer and their families in the most positive ways." Mrs. Wiemers

"At SMS, our students strive to be respectful and responsible. I believe our students work hard to be kind and live the TIGER way each day." Mrs. Delaney

"Johnson Elementary student's display Tiger Pride each day. They are safe, responsible, respectful and kind. We are proud to be our student's teachers." Mrs. McGuire

"Fairview students are caring, hard-working and great to be around!" Mr. Olson
#studentappreciationday

Spencer Schools- Breakfast & Lunch Options for Children

The Spencer Community School District is offering breakfast and lunch while our schools are closed over the next few weeks.

Starting Thursday, March 19.

‚ÄúGrab and Go‚Äù cold breakfast and lunch will be provided for all children ages 18 and under.

Meals will be available Monday through Friday from 8:00 to 9:00 a.m. until further notice.
Children will pick up both breakfast and lunch at this time.
Meals will be available to be picked up at the following locations:
Johnson Elementary (near the main entrance)
Fairview Elementary (near the main entrance)
Lincoln Elementary (near the main entrance)
Spencer High School (entrance #10 -Northwest side of the building)

post_text:
Hello-

Tonight, Governor Reynolds made the recommendation for schools to close for the next four weeks. This is due to the expanding threat of the coronavirus. Spencer Schools will be closed for the next four weeks. We will not have classes until at least Monday, April 13th.

All school activities are suspended until further notice. School Buildings will not be open until at least April 13th.

Also, we are working on providing "Grab and Go" breakfast and lunches at several school sites. We will notify you of when that program will start and provide more details as soon as we have those plans solidified.

We will continue to provide information as we move through the next several weeks.

Sincerely,

Terry Hemann, Superintendent

post_text: A big thank you to all our local businesses that volunteered their time to participate in The Game of Life at the high school. Seniors spent the morning learning about all aspects of life including buying a home, learning about loans and checking accounts, budgeting for luxuries such as gym memberships and cell phones and learning the importance of still being charitable to your community. Local law enforcement was also present to talk about the dangers of drug and alcohol use and it's effect on your decision-making and motor skills.

Congratulations to our High School boys swimmers that competed at the State Swim meet this past Saturday in Iowa City. Ethan Heiter, Connor Tigges, Cole DeVlaeminck and Reid Tigges represented Spencer in the 200 free relay finishing in 7th place with a new school record!

Individually, Ethan Heiter finished 12th place in the 50 free with a new school record and Reid Tigges finished 24th. Connor Tigges finished 13th in the 100 backstroke. Great job swimmers representing our school and community!!

post_text: Congrats to the Tiger boys swim team who competed in Districts this past Saturday at Fort Dodge! They had many great performances amongst the whole team and several that advanced to the IHSAA State Meet this weekend. The 200 Medley Relay qualified for the state meet and broke the school record from 2009 with a time of 1:40.00 swam by Ethan Heiter, Cole DeVlaeminck, Reid Tigges, and Connor Tigges. The same 4 boys also qualified for state in the 200 Free Relay and broke the school record from 2011 with a time of 1:28.61. Reid Tigges, Connor Tigges and Ethan Heiter all qualified for events individually as well! Great job this season to the entire boys swim team, and good luck at state on February 15!

post_text:
A message from The Spencer Community School Foundation:
THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU
On behalf of the Spencer Community School Foundation, we would like thank the team of community volunteers that made the famous Tiger Pa performance last Friday night a huge success. We live in such a generous and supportive community, which was displayed at the annual foundation Tiger Pa ‚Äúfun‚Äù raiser!
Thank you to all of our sponsors, volunteers, spectators and of course the 23 dads (cowgirls) that gave up their time, talents, fashion expertise and treasures to come out and dance for $$. Their goal was to raise funds (and make their children proud) to benefit Spencer Community School students. More than $15,000 was raised and will be used for student and classroom experiences and opportunities. Thank you to everyone... together, we can make a difference. #tigerkind

post_text: Interact, a high school service club through the Spencer Rotary Club, is hosting a clothing drive! Please drop off all lightly worn clothing/coats at Friday's home basketball games against Cherokee! The drive will be located at the admissions table throughout the girl's and boys' games. All winter clothing will be donated to Upper Des Moines, with other clothing donations going to Grand Community Outreach.
